of expertise and whether he would be interested in such a mandate. His
response was positive. No other agreement has occurred. <br>
<br>
I do not see how we would have work for a full-time lawyer at the Regional
Board. <br>
<br>
What we saw in the last five years, from time to time we need the help
of a lawyer regarding working conditions when we have to dismiss an employe=
e,
we usually go with a specialized lawer in that field. <br>
Occasionally we had to consult a lawyer concerning the elections. <br>
And in our negotiations with the MSSS on our &nbsp;Strategic Regional Plan
(SRP) we had a lawyer. <br>
<br>
I think in the process that will take us to NRG we should hire a lawyer
&nbsp;that would be available when we need and that would be paid at an
hourly rate. </font>
